The Obelisk of Axum, was itself collapsed and broken when it was found by Italian soldiers at the end of 1935, following the Italian conquest of Ethiopia. It had fallen in the 4th century and had broken into five pieces. In 1937, it was taken as war booty and moved to Italy by the Fascist regime, which wanted to commemorate the conquest of Ethiopia and the birth of the ephemeral "new Roman Empire."

It arrived via ship in Naples (on a boat called the Adua), on March 27, 1937. It was then transported to Rome, where it was reassembled and erected on Porta Capena square in front of the Ministry for Italian Africa (later the headquarters of the United Nations's Food and Agriculture Organization) and the Circus Maximus. It was officially unveiled on October 28 1937 to commemorate the 15th anniversary of the March on Rome. The operation was coordinated by Ugo Monneret de Villard.
The Lion of Judah, a bronze statue and symbol of the Ethiopian monarchy, was taken along with the obelisk and displayed in front of Termini railway station.

In one heated fight, Eunice confronts Steve or allegations of his cheating. "I seen you chasing her 'round the balcony--I'm gonna call the vice squad" (Williams, 75). When Steve denies her allegations and advances, she exclaims, "You hit me! I'm gonna call the police!" (75). She doesn't call the police, and instead runs to the local bar, as her husband runs after her.

Later in the scene, we see Eunice and Steve return. "[Steve and Eunice come around corner. Steve's arm is around Eunice's shoulder and she is sobbing luxuriously and he is cooing love-words. There is a murmur of thunder as they go slowly upstairs in a tight embrace]" (78). Williams made it a point by adding "tight embrace", that even though they fought, they've come together again as if nothing happened.
The fight, which turned the relationship bad, ends up being good as both parties make up and move on.

Nature is the genetic makeup encoded in your DNA where information for every type of characteristic is passed on. For example, if both creators have green eyes, then their offspring will most likely have green eyes as well because it is the dominant trait. Nurture is the environment factors the individual is exposed to. For example, is the child is encourage to read daily, then the child will grow up loving to read.

This picture shows the link between heredity and the environment. The mother and father have the trait to roll their tongues therefore because of genetics, the son is able to do it as well. The role that the environment plays in this picture is that even though some are able to roll their tongue, it doesn't mean that others will enjoy seeing it. People's decisions affects how the inherit traits are used.

This concept of nature and nurture is important to me because it affects everyone's future. The way people express themselves based on their heredity and environment is who they become as individuals. It also interest me because my parents are loud and stubborn, but I am quiet and reasonable. This may be because of the environment I grew up and my peers. Also, everyone in my family can roll their tongue but I can not. Now why is that?
SOURCE-  Haskings-Winner, Jan, and Rachel Collishaw. "Heredity and Environment; Pg.200,204 &205."Social Science: An Introduction. Toronto, ON: McGraw-Hill Ryerson, 2011.

Recipe:
Pre-Heat oven to 375
Coat bottom and sides of 8x8 glass pan with a little butter

Ingredients:
3 or 4 large Granny Smith Apples
6T sugar separated 
2 T Cinnamon
6T brown sugar separated
3/4 c flour
6T cold butter to cut into flour

Peel and core apples.  Slice in to various bite site pieces.
Put in sauce pan and sprinkle 3T of sugar and 3T of brown sugar, and 1 T of Cinnamon, stir to coat apples
Cook over med-heat until softened about 10 minutes. Stirring to coat the apples.  Drain a bit into sink at the end.

Combine flour, 3T of sugar,  1T of Cinnamon in bowl.  Stir.  Slowly cut in cold butter and make crumbles with a fork or fingers.

Place the apples in the bottom of the 8x8 dish and spread evenly.  Pour the crumbles over the top.  Sprinkle with Cinnamon and then sprinkle with brown sugar.

Bake in over for 30 minutes.  Spoon onto a plate next to vanilla ice cream or by itself :)

» 4 tortillas

» Zanahoria
» Repollo

Preparación

Untá cuatro tortillas con cuatro cucharadas de salsa golf. Colocá en un extremo tiritas de pollo previamente cocidas, hojas de lechuga, zanahoria rallada y repollo cortado finamente en juliana. Salpimentá a gusto. Cerrá cuidadosamente envolviendo los rollitos con papel film y llevá a la heladera durante no menos de una hora.
